<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.001C13/87: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Governor of Texas</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moody</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-16">December 16, 1929</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:40
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your wire 14th. I feel confident that Mr. Valls will make no attempt to
                            have a warrant of arrest served on General Calles when he passes through
                            Texas en route to Mexico.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dan Moody</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>